==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Herpes
<hw>Her"pes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>"e`rphs</grk>, fr. <grk>"e`rpein</grk> to creep.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An eruption of the skin, taking various names,
according to its form, or the part affected, caused by a herpesvirus
infection; especially, an eruption of vesicles in small distinct
clusters, accompanied with itching or tingling, including shingles,
ringworm, and the like; -- so called from its tendency to creep or
spread from one part of the skin to another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Herpes simplex</ent>⟦br⟧
